	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=18695><span id= >Loeb</span></a><br><span id=notbold>7 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Get that pocket. It only has 4 pockets, fill one with food, one with water, 2 with bandages.&nbsp;&nbsp;Then carry 0.3 stone on you). If the pocket goes, you lose nothing you wouldn't have already lost anyway.<br><br>Get Fire shield. Cast it on yourself and see how long the spell REALLY lasts.  Far longer than the visual effect. Always cast on your pet and you prior to a battle.  Or at lower levels, on your pet.<br><br>KEEP THAT PET BUFFED AND HEALED. Make sure you keep Burnout on your pet at all times, and Renew Elements handy.  Heal them before you med after a battle.  That way they can protect you.  Doesn't do any good to have a half dead gaurd dog.<br>Earth pets have a high HP, but they are really slow. If you have a MOB hitting rapidly they die easily. Water is my preferred tank for soloing.  Earth I use when I have a caster strong group.<br><br>Get yourself some armour and be willing to take hits for your pet. I can step in, take a bub of dmg and step out, my pet's healed.  They heal 10 times faster then a PC.<br><br>I leveled 3 levels in Timorous Deep. My tactic for soloing Ogres?  Sort of a kite.  I cast dmg shield on my pet and myself. Hit the MOB with the highest dd spell I could so they agroed on me instead of the pet.  Sent the pet after them before they got to me and hit them with a second dd spell.  Ran backward facing them once they got to me trying to stay just out of reach.  When they hit me for a full bub of dmg, I charged straight over them and behind the pet.  By this time the pet's taunt had them hooked. I hit with a couple lighter dd spells, and let the pet finish them off.<br><br>TAKE SOME HITS FOR THAT PET. He saves your life more often than you know but the first gripe I hear from newbies is that he dies too fast. Don't let him. Get some armor and keep him fighting for you.<br><br>PP? Learn a skill. And kill wisps in East and West Commons. The GLS' sell for 5 - 7 pp each.  Lightstones sell for 1 pp.<br><br>Loeb Rahl<br>24 Magi<br>Knights of the Griffin<br>Drinal Server</p>&nbsp;<br>-----------<br>Loeb Rahl<br>Elementalist in his 51st season of specialization<br>Divine Intervention<br>Drin</td></tr>
